                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-defend2797" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18300916-344-off1765" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-off1765" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-off1765" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18300916-344-cd1766" type="crimeDate">13th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-344-off1765 t18300916-344-cd1766"></join>, one 10l. Bank note
            </rs>, the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t18300916-344-victim2799" type="victimName">
                     Henry 
                     Pickford
                  <interp inst="t18300916-344-victim2799" type="surname" value="Pickford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-victim2799" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-victim2799" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-344-off1765 t18300916-344-victim2799"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>ELIZABETH PICKFORD. I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18300916-344-person2800">
                  Henry 
                  Pickford
               <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2800" type="surname" value="Pickford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2800" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2800" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; he is in the 3rd regiment of Foot Guards. On the 12th of July, the prisoner was <rs id="t18300916-344-deflabel1767" type="occupation">pot-boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-344-defend2797 t18300916-344-deflabel1767"></join> at the Canteen, in Portman-street - my husband is <rs id="t18300916-344-viclabel1768" type="occupation">pay-serjeant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-344-victim2799 t18300916-344-viclabel1768"></join> of his company; the prisoner came that evening to know if I wanted any beer - I told him what beer to bring, and told him to ask his master to give me change for a 10l. note; he returned with the beer, and said I could not have the change that evening, but as early as six o'clock in the morning I might; I said I did not want it so soon, when my husband came off duty would be time enough - he came the next morning, and asked if I had the paper; I then gave him the note to get the change, and never saw him afterwards till he was apprehended on the 17th of August - I never got the note or the money.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HEATON. Q. Did not you say you gave him the note that evening? A. No, in the morning; I asked if I could have the change - I never saw him after I gave it into his hand - I positively swear that; I will swear he did not come back, say his master could not give me change, and I tell him to get change elsewhere - I saw him go towards his master's with the note; I believe my husband had leave from Mr. Conant to compromise the matter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-344-person2801">
                  HENRY 
                  PEARSON
               <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2801" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2801" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2801" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the publican. The prisoner came to me with the note, and asked if I could give change - I said I could not; he went away, and came back in ten minutes and asked again - I said I could not; he said he must go and get change; he went out, and did not return.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had he the note with him? A. Yes, the second time, but not the first - he asked for change for Mrs. Pickford.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-344-person2802">
                  DANIEL 
                  CHAPMAN
               <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2802" type="surname" value="CHAPMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2802" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2802" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent for to apprehend the prisoner on the 17th of August - I asked if he had had the note; he said Yes, and he had spent it - that as soon as he found his master could not give him change, he saw some soldiers, and said to them, "Come along with me, and have a spree, I have plenty of money now."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-344-person2803">
                  JOB 
                  JEFFRIES
               <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2803" type="surname" value="JEFFRIES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2803" type="given" value="JOB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-344-person2803" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a corporal in the 3rd regiment of Guards. The prisoner came to me on the morning of the 13th of July, a little before ten o'clock; he had some money in his hand, and asked me to give him some more to get a pot of beer - I said I would not; in about ten minutes he came again, and said he had a 10l. note.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you attend the first examination? A. No, but the serjeant asked me about it one morning - I attended on the last examination; this was on Tuesday morning, the 13th of July - I remember it very well; I will swear it was Tuesday, the 13th of July.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 25.</p>
               <p>
